{"TopicId":176159,"ForumId":55,"TopicTitle":"Mouse position doesn\u0026#039;t agree with button locations in 1.4.4","CreatedByName":"ianyikos","CreatedById":70660,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-24T21:53:50Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"ianyikos","CreatedById":70660,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-24T21:53:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn the latest update the mouse pointer position does not agree with the button locations, it has to be slightly off, and it\u0027s impossible to adjust the resolution because I can\u0027t push the button.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ianyikos","CreatedById":70660,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-24T22:08:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNevermind, it works now.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vanamonde","CreatedById":27914,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-27T22:37:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOkay then. \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"katateochi","CreatedById":35181,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-06-27T23:26:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI noticed this when running in windowed mode. In full screen it was fine, but when windowed, as \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/70660-ianyikos/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002270660\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/70660-ianyikos/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@ianyikos\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0said, the mouse needs to be offset (by about the height of the button) to be able to click it. I\u0027m guessing the height of the offset error would equal the height of the window title bar.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DunnoAnyThing","CreatedById":180004,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-07-06T00:04:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223406455\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022176159\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221530141972\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002235181\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022katateochi\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 6/28/2018 at 8:26 AM, katateochi said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI noticed this when running in windowed mode. In full screen it was fine, but when windowed, as \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/70660-ianyikos/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002270660\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/70660-ianyikos/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@ianyikos\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0said, the mouse needs to be offset (by about the height of the button) to be able to click it. I\u0027m guessing the height of the offset error would equal the height of the window title bar.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYep, same thing for me. So I use fullscreen all the time, but it\u0027s kinda hard to use other online tools in this state.\u003Cbr\u003E\nSo, maybe a fix might be needed?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JAFO","CreatedById":132901,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-07-09T01:19:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223411050\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022176159\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221530835471\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022180004\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DunnoAnyThing\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 7/6/2018 at 10:04 AM, DunnoAnyThing said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI use fullscreen all the time, but \u003Cstrong\u003Eit\u0027s kinda hard to use other online tools in this state\u003C/strong\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s what alt-tab is for.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DunnoAnyThing","CreatedById":180004,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-07-09T02:27:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223412505\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022176159\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221531099174\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022132901\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022JAFO\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, JAFO said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s what \u003Cstrong\u003Ealt-tab\u003C/strong\u003E is for.\u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYep, that method is\u00A0what I\u0027m currently using - but I bet this isn\u0027t a desired situation(or at least planned to be.), so maybe a fix might be good(but not \u0027essential\u0027).\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nPlus, I think this behavior is not specific to 1.4.4, since IIRC I had to use Fullscreen in all versions(can\u0027t remember back when 1.3.0 was the latest, though.)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-07-09T02:29:07Z\u0022 title=\u002207/09/2018 02:29  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 9, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by DunnoAnyThing\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JAFO","CreatedById":132901,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-07-09T02:45:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223412525\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022176159\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221531103254\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022180004\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DunnoAnyThing\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n19 minutes ago, DunnoAnyThing said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI bet this isn\u0027t a desired situation(or at least planned to be.)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGiven that alt-tab is the standard way of handling this kind of situation,\u00A0\u003Cem\u003Efor pretty much the entire IT industry\u003C/em\u003E, I\u0027d imagine it \u003Cstrong\u003Eis\u003C/strong\u003E planned to be exactly as-is.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEdit: alternatively, you could always try adding a second monitor to your computer... that would work too...\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:wink:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-07-09T02:47:31Z\u0022 title=\u002207/09/2018 02:47  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 9, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by JAFO\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DunnoAnyThing","CreatedById":180004,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-07-09T02:51:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223412531\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022176159\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221531104335\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022132901\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022JAFO\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, JAFO said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGiven that alt-tab is the standard way of handling this kind of situation,\u00A0\u003Cem\u003Efor pretty much the entire IT industry\u003C/em\u003E, I\u0027d imagine it \u003Cstrong\u003Eis\u003C/strong\u003E planned to be exactly as-is.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI mean, Alt-tab itself is indeed pretty much standard behavior, but KSP\u0027s behavior(mouse click not interpreted correctly) is not intended. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JAFO","CreatedById":132901,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-07-09T02:53:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223412534\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022176159\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221531104692\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022180004\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DunnoAnyThing\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, DunnoAnyThing said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKSP\u0027s behavior(mouse click not interpreted correctly) is not intended\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFair point.. and one worth submitting a bug-report over, IMO.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}